Clayton K. Yeutter
Clayton Keith Yeutter, ONZM served as United States Secretary of Agriculture under President George H. W. Bush from 1989 to 1991 before serving as Counselor to the President in 1992. He served as United States Trade Representative from 1985 to 1989 and as Chairman for the Republican National Committee from 1991 until 1992. Yeutter was employed as a Senior Advisor at the international law firm Hogan Lovells in Washington, D.C. Wikipedia*
On the C-SPAN Networks:Clayton K. Yeutter has 66 videos in the C-SPAN Video Library; the first appearance was a 1986 Call-In. The year with the most videos was 1991 with 17 videos as a Secretary for the Department of Agriculture. The year with the highest average number of views per program was 2013 with an average of 379 views per program. Most appearances with George H. W. Bush (5), Mickey Kantor (5), Charles "Charlie" R. Black Jr. (3). Most common tags: International Trade, Republican Party, Agriculture.
