Executive Profile
Clayton K. Yeutter Ph.D.Fund Advisor, Cultivian Sandbox Ventures, LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 25 different industries.See Board Relationships86--
Background

		Dr. Clayton K. Yeutter, Ph.D., has been Counsel, Attorney and Senior Advisor of Hogan & Hartson LLP since June 1993. Dr. Yeutter focuses on issues of international trade, food and agriculture. He serves as a Fund Advisor of Cultivian Sandbox Ventures, LP. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of the Chicago Mercantile Exchange from 1978 to 1985. From 1985 to 1988, he served as U.S. Trade Representative. Dr. Yeutter served as the U.S. Secretary of Agriculture ... from 1989 to 1991 and served in cabinet and sub-cabinet posts under four U.S. President. In 1970s, he held three sub cabinet positions in the Nixon and Ford Administrations as Assistant Secretary of Agriculture for Marketing and Consumer Services, Assistant Secretary of Agriculture for International Affairs and Commodity Programs from 1974 to 1975 and Deputy Special Trade Representative for Trade Negotiations from 1975 to 1977. Dr. Yeutter serves as Chairman of the Board at CropSolutions, Inc. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Oppenheimer Funds and its fund complex. He served as the Chairman of Commercial Barge Line Company (formerly, American Commercial Lines Inc.) from January 11, 2005 to December 21, 2010. He served as Chairman of Board at ACL I Corporation. He served as Chairman of the Board of Trustees at OFI Tremont Core Strategies Hedge Fund since 2003. He serves as a Trustee of OppenheimerFunds, Inc. Dr. Yeutter has been Director of Covanta since October 2007. He serves as a Director of Weyerhauser Corporation. He has been an Independent Manager of Burlington Capital Group LLC , General Partner of America First Multifamily Investors, L.P. since 2001. He has been a Director at Covanta Energy Asia Pacific Holdings Ltd. since July 2002. He serves as a Director of Chicago Climate Exchange, Inc. Dr. Yeutter has been a Non-executive Director of Zurich and Allied Zurich p.l.c. since March 1998 and as a Non-executive Director of Zurich Allied AG since September 1998. He serves as a Director of Zurich Financial Services (Switzerland), B.A.T. Industries Ltd., a tobacco and financial services; ConAgra Inc., and formerly (in descending chronological order) IMC Global Inc. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board at ZANA Network, LLC. He served as a Director of Neogen Corp. since October 2007 until October 6, 2016. He served as a Director of Covanta Holding Corporation (formerly, Danielson Holding Corp.) from July 2002 to May 6, 2010. He served as Director of Oppenheimer Funds and its fund complex. He served as Trustee of OFI Tremont Market Neutral Hedge Fund. He served as Manager of The Burlington Capital Group LLC since 2001. Dr. Yeutter served as a Manager of America First Companies LLC, the Manager of America First Capital Source I LLC and America First Real Estate Investment Partners LP since 2001. He served as a Manager of America First of America First Apartment Investors Inc. He served as a Director of Farmers Group, Inc. (also known as Farmers Insurance Group Inc and FGI) since 1994. Dr. Yeutter served as a non-executive director of B.A.T from January 1993 to September 1998. Dr. Yeutter served as a Director of Weyerhaeuser Co. from 1999 to April 2004. He served as a Director of Caterpillar Inc., from 1993 to December 2002, ConAgra Foods, Inc. from 1993 to 2001; Texas Instruments Inc. from 1993 to 2001 and FMC Corp. from 1993 to 2001. He served as Independent Trustee of OFI Tremont Core Strategies Hedge Fund since 2005. From 1991 to 1992, he served as the Chairman of the Republican National Committee and returned to the Bush Administration as a Counselor to the President since 1992. Dr. Yeutter holds a B.S., J.D., and a Ph.D. in Agricultural Economics from University of Nebraska, both with highest academic honors.Read Full Background




